</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[115,770,187,1139]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
MA 334586 was annotated as “lectotype” by A.L. Cabrera 1971 but the lectotypification was never published. This specimen (
<figureCitation box="[232,312,836,860]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[130,162,1926,1945]" captionTargetBox="[253,1353,185,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[253,1353,185,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. a, neotype of Solanum cymosum Ortega (=Solanum lanceolatum Cav.) (MA 476353); b, neotype of Solanum ficifolium Ortega (= Solanum ferrugineum Jacq.) (MA 334586); c, neotype of Solanum leprosum Ortega (=Solanum elaeagnifolium Cav.) (MA 334600); d, neotype of Solanum subbiflorum Ortega (=Solanum capense L.) (MA308482)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6327660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6327660/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) has a label with “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ortega" authorityName="Ortega" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">Solanum ficifolium Ortega</taxonomicName>
/ ex Hort. Reg. Matr. anno 1803” in hand of José Demetrio Rodriguez and is a young flowering plant with sinuate leaves and three inflorescences (one of which is branched). This sheet best matches Ortega’s protologue which mentions both sinuate leaves and branched inflorescences and so is here selected as the neotype (
<figureCitation box="[431,509,1022,1046]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[130,162,1926,1945]" captionTargetBox="[253,1353,185,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[253,1353,185,1906]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. a, neotype of Solanum cymosum Ortega (=Solanum lanceolatum Cav.) (MA 476353); b, neotype of Solanum ficifolium Ortega (= Solanum ferrugineum Jacq.) (MA 334586); c, neotype of Solanum leprosum Ortega (=Solanum elaeagnifolium Cav.) (MA 334600); d, neotype of Solanum subbiflorum Ortega (=Solanum capense L.) (MA308482)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6327660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6327660/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
). Although this juvenile plant lacks the diagnostic fruiting pedicels, the stems and inflorescences have the glandular stellate trichomes characteristic of 
<taxonomicName box="[203,358,1115,1139]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis box="[203,358,1115,1139]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. ferrugineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
